By combining detection and masking techniques, you can effectively identify and mitigate the use of browser-based mining scripts. Detection involves analyzing network traffic patterns and using advanced tools and models, while masking involves obfuscating and anonymizing the traffic to make it less conspicuous. This balanced approach ensures that mining activity is both detectable and stealthy.
